"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The `sns.heatmap` function expects a 2D dataset that can be coerced into an ndarray. The 'tips' dataset loaded from seaborn is a DataFrame with multiple columns, but it is not a 2D array suitable for a heatmap directly. The heatmap function requires a 2D array-like structure, typically a pivot table or a correlation matrix derived from the DataFrame.\",\n  \"patch\": \"5c5\\n< g = sns.heatmap(tips, square=True, cbar_kws={'fraction': 0.01}, cmap='OrRd', linewidth=1)\\n---\\n> g = sns.heatmap(tips.pivot_table(index='sex', columns='day', values='total_bill', aggfunc='mean'), square=True, cbar_kws={'fraction': 0.01}, cmap='OrRd', linewidth=1)\"\n}"